% @MCCODE_PREFIX@PLOTDIFF-html(1)
% @FLAVOR_UPPER@ @MCCODE_PARTICLE@ Ray Tracing Team
% @MCCODE_DATE@

# NAME

**@MCCODE_PREFIX@plotdiff-html** - Plotting the difference between two @MCCODE_NAME@ simulation results in a browser

# SYNOPSIS

**@MCCODE_PREFIX@plotdiff-html** [-h] [-n] [-l] [--autosize] [--libpath [LIBPATH ...]] [-o OUTPUT] [-A LABEL_A] [-B LABEL_B] [-W WIDTH] [-H HEIGHT] a b

# DESCRIPTION

The front-end **@MCCODE_PREFIX@plotdiff-html** is a program that produces plots of the
*difference* between the monitors of two @MCCODE_NAME@ simulation results, i.e.
`diff.monN = a.monN - b.monN` for every monitor output file `monN` that is
present, with matching binning, in both simulation results `a` and `b`. This
is useful to quickly spot how two simulation runs differ, e.g. after a
component or parameter change, a McCode version upgrade, or comparing MPI vs.
non-MPI results.

`a` and `b` may each be either a simulation output directory (as produced by
`@MCCODE_PREFIX@run`, containing a `mccode.sim` file) or a single monitor data
file. Only monitors present in both `a` and `b`, with identical binning, are
compared; monitors found in only one of the two inputs, or with mismatched
binning, are skipped with a warning.

For 1D monitors, the difference curve is plotted with error bars computed
from standard error propagation. For 2D monitors, since differences can be
both positive and negative, a diverging blue/white/red colour scale centred
on zero is used instead of the ordinary mcplot-html colour scale; blue is
negative (`b` bigger than `a`), white is (approximately) zero, and red is
positive (`a` bigger than `b`). The "log" variant of a 2D plot uses a signed
(symlog-style) transform so that small differences remain visible while
preserving their sign.

This is the web/html difference-plotting tool (in browser), and reuses the
same client-side plotting code as **@MCCODE_PREFIX@plot-html**.

# OPTIONS

**-h, --help**
:   show this help message and exit

**-n, --nobrowse**
:   do not open a webbrowser viewer

**-l, --log**
:   when comparing two single monitor files, also produce a log-style plot.
    (When comparing two simulation folders, both a linear and a log-style
    plot are always produced for every monitor, just like
    **@MCCODE_PREFIX@plot-html**.)

**--autosize**
:   expand to window size on load

**--libpath [LIBPATH ...]**
:   js lib files path

**-o OUTPUT, --output OUTPUT**
:   specify output directory for the generated plots (default:
    `diff_<a>_vs_<b>` in the current directory)

**-A LABEL_A, --label-a LABEL_A**
:   short label used for simulation `a` in titles and filenames (default:
    the basename of `a`)

**-B LABEL_B, --label-b LABEL_B**
:   short label used for simulation `b` in titles and filenames (default:
    the basename of `b`)

**-W WIDTH, --width WIDTH**
:   width of iframes

**-H HEIGHT, --height HEIGHT**
:   height of iframes

# FILES

/usr/share/@FLAVOR@/resources
/usr/share/@FLAVOR@/tools/Python/mccodelib/mccode_config.json
~/.@FLAVOR@/mccode_config.json
http://www.@FLAVOR@.org

# EXAMPLES

Run the *Test_SX* example (Single crystal diffraction) twice with different parameters, and plot the difference
:   - `@MCCODE_PREFIX@run Test_SX.instr -d output_a -n 1e7 TTH=13.4`
:   - `@MCCODE_PREFIX@run Test_SX.instr -d output_b -n 1e7 TTH=14.0`
:   - `@MCCODE_PREFIX@plotdiff-html output_a output_b`

